        "Method 1: Try to make denominator 10, 100, or 1000.",
        "If impossible, use Method 2: Long division with decimal places.",
        "Step 1: Set up division bracket: 3)1.000000 with decimal point in quotient above decimal in dividend.",
        "Step 2: Since 3 > 1, add a zero: 3)1.0 becomes 3)10. Divide: 10 ÷ 3 = 3 remainder 1. Write 0.3 above.",
        "Step 3: Bring down next zero to make 10 again. Divide: 10 ÷ 3 = 3 remainder 1. Write 0.33 above.",
        "Step 4: Continue pattern. Bring down next zero to make 10. Divide: 10 ÷ 3 = 3 remainder 1. Write 0.333 above.",
        "Step 5: Notice the pattern: remainder is always 1, quotient digit is always 3.",
        "Step 6: Conclude: 1/3 = 0.333... = 0.3̄ (3 repeats forever)."
        ]
      
